<br>
No I was not.  I don't think we were created, I don't think it was done equally and I think the rights we enjoy were hard won, not just given.  <br>
<br>
I have worked in too many ARC centers and tutored too many handicapped kids to think we all got dealt an even hand.  I know too many kids who were more privileged than I to think my hand is that superior.  I read too many 'baby dies locked in car' stories to think there is some fairness to it all.  I watch our president Dubyah wipe his ...feet... on our constitution to often to think these rights are inalienable.  All it takes is an act of congress.  We get the cards we are dealt, we make the best hand we can of them.  No gods, no plan, just old fashioned luck.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;You could only remove Darwin from the books he is actually in. &quot;<br>
<br>
Why would you remove Darwin from the science books that he is in?  He does not endorse a religion, he does not refute one.  He identified a factual set of patterns, and provided the best answer to those patterns then submitted it to the scrutiny of the larger scientific community who hammered it from all sides, revising and refining as they did.  Evolution is one of the single strongest and most evidence supported principles in science.  Are you asking that we ignore the facts and set them aside in the name of your religion?  Is that preferable to teaching the science of biology in a biology class from which all our medical advancements spring?  This <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>IS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the baby with the bathwater here if you are.  <br>
<br>
The government has a constitutional obligation not to endorse one religion over another.  It does not have an obligation to revise history or edit truth to protect the tenets of a religion from scrutiny.  This would be the same as the Raelians asking astronomy teachers not to discuss what is really in the tail of a comet; or Nazi’s to get the holocaust revised in the history books to say they didn’t kill Jews.  Evolution is in the science books because it is a valid, tested and thoroughly established scientific force, not some subversive plot to undermine xianity.  You want to raise your child in ignorance of science, do so, but don’t expect the government to have to help you, majority or not.<br>
<br>
The fact that evolution happens is not under debate in the realm of science.  Look at any major publication or scientific journal.  You don’t see articles or studies submitted for peer review suggesting a replacement to evolution.  You see many discussing the specific mechanics of HOW it operates, but not the fact that it IS operating.  That is because, unless or until a better solution is presented, the matter is settled.  The same way our heliocentric solar system and the molecular weight of water is settled.  Produce a fact not explained by the theory and a solution that explains all the other facts and the exception better and you’ll get a Nobel Prize.<br>
<br>
You imply there is some debate over the ‘theory of evolution’ yet it is as valid as the ‘theory of uniform gravitation’ or the ‘theory of quantum relativity.’  This is not some trumped up opinion no matter how much people try to obfuscate it.  <br>
<br>
Fact: organism reproduction produces differences in offspring.  <br>
Fact: differences that create a competitive advantage increase the chances of survival and reproduction.<br>
Fact: reproduction of differences accumulate over time.<br>
Fact: after enough time, the differences are enough that the original organisms cannot breed.<br>
<br>
That’s evolution in a nutshell (change over time.)  Humans and apes share a common ancestor.  We are not siblings.  No ape will give birth to a person, no person will give birth to an ape.   The ancestor we share also shares ancestors further back with polar bears and tigers.  Further back still they share them with dinosaurs and even fish.  You can demonstrate evolution by selective breeding in the lab using insects, reptiles, amphibians and mammals.  There are no roving bands of wild miniature poodles because they were bred selectively by HUMANS.  Evolution is change over time, forces for it are any selection process, be they natural or man-made.  Try and force that out of the school system and eliminate the purpose of having one.<br>
<br>
